name: Air North 737-2X6A Combi [C-GANV] Pushback, Taxi, and Takeoff from Calgary Airport ᴴᴰ
description:
What better way to commemorate the 50th anniversary of the 737's first flight than with a classic 737? Here we have Air North's sole 737-200 pushing back, taxiing, and taking off from Calgary International Airport on a special charter flight to Cranbrook. Sorry about all the wind noise, but I was on top of a 7 story parkade and it was exceptionally windy that day. ATC is included, hope you enjoy!

Thanks for watching!
